ta\";s:3:\"SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"content\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"content marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"stats\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://theseedstudio.com/?p=318\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:354:\"You may have heard that when it comes to online marketing, content is king. 87% of all businesses are engaged in some form of <strong>content marketing</strong>. There are 3 good reasons for this.\n\nFirst, people trust blog posts, videos and&#8230; <a href=\"http://theseednetwork.com/blog/2011/06/17/content-marketing/\" class=\"read_more\">Read the rest</a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Dan Logtenberg\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4495:\"<p>You may have heard that when it comes to online marketing, content is king. <a title=\"Content Marketing Report\" href=\"http://www.contentmarketinginstitute.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/B2B-Content-Marketing-2010-Small-Organization-Report.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">87% of all businesses</a> are engaged in some form of <strong>content marketing</strong>. There are 3 good reasons for this.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://theseednetwork.com/blog/2011/06/17/content-marketing/content/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-320\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-320\" title=\"content\" src=\"http://theseednetwork.com/wp-content/uploads/content.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p>First, people trust blog posts, videos and reviews more than they trust advertising. 60-70% of users are more likely to buy something after reading a post or watching a video about it than after seeing an ad.</p>\n<p>Second, content marketing is essential to improving search engine ranking. Every post you create gets indexed by Google, Bing and others, increasing your exposure for that topic and improving your website&#8217;s overall search ranking. Ads, on the other hand are essentially invisible to search engines and have no long term impact on search ranking at all.</p>\n<p>And third, in most cases, content marketing is also less expensive than advertising.</p>\n<h2>First, the Hard Part.</h2>\n<p>So, if content marketing has more impact AND is cheaper, why isn&#8217;t everyone doing it?</p>\n<p>For most people, content is a lot harder to create than an ad.Â You might be great at running your business and passionate about what you do, but if you&#8217;re like a lot of entrepreneurs, you clam up when you try to write it down. Creating interesting and original content takes time, and most entrepreneurs aren&#8217;t natural writers.</p>\n<h2>The W5 Content Solution</h2>\n<p>The easiest and arguably best way to create content is simply to answer one or more of these Â questions:Â <strong>&#8220;Who?&#8221;</strong>,Â <strong>&#8220;What?&#8221;</strong>,<strong>&#8220;When?&#8221;</strong>,Â <strong>&#8220;Where?&#8221;</strong>,Â <strong>&#8220;Why?&#8221;</strong> orÂ <strong>&#8220;How?&#8221;</strong></p>\n<p>There are probably thousands of W questions related to your business that you can answer right now. If you&#8217;re still stuck, think about the questions your customers ask every day about your products or services.</p>\n<h3>The Forumla:</h3>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a formula for creating content that works for me:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Every time someone asks me a question about our services, company or Â industry, I write it down. I also pay attention to the answer I give and any follow-up questions and I write them down too.</li>\n<li>I make a bulleted list of my answer, trying to make it as simple and clear as possible.</li>\n<li>I write down where the question comes from. I might explain the story of the customer Â or I might give some broader context. For example, do a lot of other people have the same question? If so, why? What does this say about my industry or service that so many people are puzzled by the same thing?</li>\n<li>When it comes time to post to your blog, all you need to do is rewrite your notes as simply and as clearly as possible.</li>\n<li>You may want to start with an anecdote or fact to better explain why the question matters and examples of how the answer can be used.</li>\n<li>Format you post: reference your statements and list your sources where possible, date your work and use sub-titles. Your readers and Google will love you for it!</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Again, keep it simple but also keep it personal. Your readers are more likely to trust you if you sound genuine.</p>\n<p>Have you tried content marketing? What worked for you?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Here are more <a href=\"http://www.bazaarvoice.com/resources/stats\" target=\"_blank\">stats on content and social media marketing</a>.</li>\n<li><a title=\"Copy Blogger\" href=\"http://copyblogger.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Copyblogger</a> has some great tips on <a title=\"Content Marketing and Copywriting\" href=\"http://www.copyblogger.com/content-marketing-copywriting/\">content marketing</a>.</li>\n<li>Remember, everything starts with a good <a title=\"Online Marketing Strategy\" href=\"http://theseedstudio.com/services/strategy-planning/\">marketing strategy</a></li>\n<li>Talk to us about our <a title=\"Internet Marketing Services\" href=\"http://theseedstudio.com/services/internet-marketing/\">Internet marketing services</a></li>\n</ul>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"http://theseednetwork.com/blog/2011/06/17/content-marketing/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"http://theseednetwork.com/blog/2011/06/17/content-marketing/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"Managing Your Email and Hosting Account with the Websitesettings.com Control Panel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/ai1ec/~3/C4Jaqr3_NKM/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a