e it\'s on the App Store. Log in to the iOS Dev Center\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 01 Sep 2010 15:25:26 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:634:\"\n<p>Game Center is Apple\'s new social gaming network that allows your users to invite friends to play a game, start a multiplayer game through auto-matching, track their achievements, and compare their best scores on a leaderboard. Learn everything you need to know about developing your apps for Game Center, from understanding the fundamentals to updating your Game Center app once it\'s on the App Store. <a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/devcenter/ios/gamecenter/index.php\" class=\"more\">Log in to the iOS Dev Center</a></p><img style=\"float:right;\" src=\"https://devimages.apple.com.edgekey.net/news/images/gamecenter.jpg\"/><br />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:59;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"New iTunes Connect Payments and Financial Reports Module\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=08252010a\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:972:\"We\'re excited to announce the new Payments and Financial Reports module in iTunes Connect. This new module provides you with details on all financial reports and payments. From a dashboard view, you can quickly obtain information including last payment, amount owed, latest monthly earnings, a rolling transaction history, unit sales, and payment trends.In addition, we\'ve also made significant updates to how your payments will be processed and how they are presented on iTunes Connect, including:Reduction in the thresholds required to be paid, increasing the frequency you will receive proceeds.A consolidated single monthly payment for all your proceeds worldwide, reducing bank fees and costs.Clearer presentation of amounts earned, amounts owed, and a reconciliation between the reported sales and the amounts paid.For more detail, read the iTunes Connect Payments & Financial Reports Guide available from the Payments and Financial Reports module in iTunes Connect.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 25 Aug 2010 10:52:45 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1125:\"\n<p>We\'re excited to announce the new Payments and Financial Reports module in iTunes Connect. This new module provides you with details on all financial reports and payments. From a dashboard view, you can quickly obtain information including last payment, amount owed, latest monthly earnings, a rolling transaction history, unit sales, and payment trends.</p><p>In addition, we\'ve also made significant updates to how your payments will be processed and how they are presented on iTunes Connect, including:</p><ul class=\"square\"><li>Reduction in the thresholds required to be paid, increasing the frequency you will receive proceeds.</li><li>A consolidated single monthly payment for all your proceeds worldwide, reducing bank fees and costs.</li><li>Clearer presentation of amounts earned, amounts owed, and a reconciliation between the reported sales and the amounts paid.</li></ul><p>For more detail, read the iTunes Connect Payments &amp; Financial Reports Guide available from the <a href=\"http://www.apple.com/itunes/go/itunesconnect/financialreports\">Payments and Financial Reports</a> module in iTunes Connect.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:60;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"Set Up Game Center Achievements and Leaderboard Categories\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=08112010a\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:330:\"You can now set up metadata for your Game Center Achievements and Leaderboard Categories in iTunes Connect. Setting up these elements will allow you to test the full capabilities of Game Center for your app in the sandbox environment.Read the Manage Game Center section of the iTunes Connect Developer Guide for more information. \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 11 Aug 2010 15:04:19 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:534:\"\n<p>You can now set up metadata for your Game Center Achievements and Leaderboard Categories in iTunes Connect. Setting up these elements will allow you to test the full capabilities of Game Center for your app in the sandbox environment.</p><p>Read the Manage Game Center section of the <a href=\"http://itunesconnect.apple.com/docs/iTunesConnect_DeveloperGuide.pdf\">iTunes Connect Developer Guide</a> for more information. </p><img style=\"float:right;\" src=\"https://devimages.apple.com.edgekey.net/news/images/gamecenter.jpg\"/><br />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:61;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"Announcing the App Store Volume Purchase Program\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=08092010a\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:395:\"We\'re pleased to announce the App Store Volume Purchase Program. Education institutions in the United States now have a new way to purchase your apps in volume for distribution to their students and faculty. You can also elect to offer special education pricing on your app when purchased in volume.Read more about the App Store Volume Purchase Program and how to get started in iTunes Connect. \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 09 Aug 2010 14:31:01 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:598:\"\n<p>We\'re pleased to announce the App Store Volume Purchase Program. Education institutions in the United States now have a new way to purchase your apps in volume for distribution to their students and faculty. You can also elect to offer special education pricing on your app when purchased in volume.</p><p><a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/appstore/volume.html\">Read more</a> about the App Store Volume Purchase Program and how to get started in iTunes Connect. </p><img style=\"float:right;\" src=\"https://devimages.apple.com.edgekey.net/news/images/feed-images/news_appstore_icon.jpg\"/><br />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:62;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"You Can Now Control When Your App Update Goes Live\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=08052010a\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:298:\"With the new Version Release Control in iTunes Connect, you can control when an updated version of your app goes live, rather than have the version go live as soon as it is approved by App Review. Read the Version Release Control section of the iTunes Connect Developer Guide for more information. \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 05 Aug 2010 12:48:39 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:396:\"\n<p>With the new Version Release Control in iTunes Connect, you can control when an updated version of your app goes live, rather than have the version go live as soon as it is approved by App Review. </p><p>Read the Version Release Control section of the <a href=\"http://itunesconnect.apple.com/docs/iTunesConnect_DeveloperGuide.pdf\">iTunes Connect Developer Guide</a> for more information. </p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:63;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"Three New App Status Indicators in iTunes Connect\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=08022010a\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1192:\"We\'ve added three new status indicators to iTunes Connect which give you a more precise indication of the state of your app when you are submitting your binary for approval. Prepare for Upload indicates that you have created a new version, but you have not yet clicked the Ready to Submit Binary button, which indicates that you are ready to deliver a binary through Application Loader. This state\'s status color is yellow. Pending Developer Release indicates that the version of your app has been approved by App Review and you have turned on the Version Release Control, but have not yet clicked Send Version Live. This state\'s status color is yellow. You should also see a pending action symbol on the version. Your version will remain in this state, and thus will not be live on the App Store until you click Send Version Live. Processing for App Store indicates that the version is being processed to go live on the App Store. Once the processing is complete, the version state will change to \"Ready for Sale.\" This state is very temporary (1-2 hours). This state\'s status color is yellow. For more information, refer to the App Store Resource Center, App Store Approval Process section.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 02 Aug 2010 15:48:40 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1366:\"\n<p>We\'ve added three new status indicators to iTunes Connect which give you a more precise indication of the state of your app when you are submitting your binary for approval. </p><p class=\"yellow\"><b>Prepare for Upload </b>indicates that you have created a new version, but you have not yet clicked the Ready to Submit Binary button, which indicates that you are ready to deliver a binary through Application Loader. This state\'s status color is yellow. </p><p class=\"yellow\"><b>Pending Developer Release</b> indicates that the version of your app has been approved by App Review and you have turned on the Version Release Control, but have not yet clicked Send Version Live. This state\'s status color is yellow. You should also see a pending action symbol on the version. Your version will remain in this state, and thus will not be live on the App Store until you click Send Version Live. </p><p class=\"yellow\"><b>Processing for App Store</b> indicates that the version is being processed to go live on the App Store. Once the processing is complete, the version state will change to \"Ready for Sale.\" This state is very temporary (1-2 hours). This state\'s status color is yellow. </p><p>For more information, refer to the App Store Resource Center, <a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/iphone/appstore/approval.html\">App Store Approval Process </a> section.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:64;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Remove Apps Using App Delete in iTunes Connect\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=07302010a\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:323:\"You can now remove any unwanted applications from your view in iTunes Connect using App Delete. There are important factors to consider when using App Delete â for example, if you want to re-use your SKU or App Name â so be sure to read the App Delete section of the iTunes Connect Developer Guide for more information.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Fri, 30 Jul 2010 13:14:08 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:414:\"\n<p>You can now remove any unwanted applications from your view in iTunes Connect using App Delete. There are important factors to consider when using App Delete â for example, if you want to re-use your SKU or App Name â so be sure to read the App Delete section of the <a href=\"http://itunesconnect.apple.com/docs/iTunesConnect_DeveloperGuide.pdf\">iTunes Connect Developer Guide</a> for more information.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:65;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"See What\'s New in the Xcode 4 Developer Preview\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=07292010a\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:479:\"iPhone and Mac Developer Program members can now download a preview of Xcode 4, the next generation of Apple\'s integrated development environment for creating iOS and Mac OS X applications. With a brand-new interface, compiler, debugger and dozens of new features, Xcode 4 is faster, easier to use, and more helpful than ever before. Quite simply, Xcode 4 will help you writer better code.Read about the many new enhancements in Xcode 4 and download the developer preview today. \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 29 Jul 2010 12:10:27 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:702:\"\n<p>iPhone and Mac Developer Program members can now download a preview of Xcode 4, the next generation of Apple\'s integrated development environment for creating iOS and Mac OS X applications. </p><p>With a brand-new interface, compiler, debugger and dozens of new features, Xcode 4 is faster, easier to use, and more helpful than ever before. Quite simply, Xcode 4 will help you writer better code.</p><p><a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/technologies/tools/whats-new.html\">Read about</a> the many new enhancements in Xcode 4 and download the developer preview today. </p><img style=\"float:right;\" src=\"https://devimages.apple.com.edgekey.net/news/images/feed-images/news_xcode_preview.png\"/><br />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:66;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"Important Information about Submitting Your Apps \nto iTunes Connect\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=07292010b\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:867:\"All binary submissions to iTunes Connect must now be uploaded using Application Loader either through Xcode\'s built-in App Submission process, or directly using the Application Loader software. This offers a significantly improved experience over uploading through iTunes Connect, including faster uploading, a more stable connection, and early validation warnings. Make sure the status of your app in iTunes Connect is Waiting for Upload before you submit your binary. Read the Distributing Applications section of the iOS Development Guide for more information about preparing your app for submission to iTunes Connect. Registered Apple Developers can also download and watch these session videos from WWDC 2010 to learn more about using Application Loader for binary submission: App Publishing with iTunes Connect Mastering Xcode for iPhone OS Development, Part I \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 29 Jul 2010 12:05:59 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1511:\"\n<p>All binary submissions to iTunes Connect must now be uploaded using Application Loader either through Xcode\'s built-in App Submission process, or directly using the Application Loader software. This offers a significantly improved experience over uploading through iTunes Connect, including faster uploading, a more stable connection, and early validation warnings. Make sure the status of your app in iTunes Connect is Waiting for Upload before you submit your binary. </p><p>Read the <a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/Xcode/Conceptual/iphone_development/145-Distributing_Applications/distributing_applications.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40007959-CH10-SW2\">Distributing Applications</a> section of the iOS Development Guide for more information about preparing your app for submission to iTunes Connect. </p><p>Registered Apple Developers can also download and watch these session videos from WWDC 2010 to learn more about using Application Loader for binary submission: </p><ul class=\"square\"><li> <a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/itunes/?destination=adc.apple.com.4088510335.04088510337.4096407267?i=1232352459\">App Publishing with iTunes Connect</a> </li><li> <a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/itunes/?destination=adc.apple.com.4088510335.04088510337.4096407249?i=1805812825\">Mastering Xcode for iPhone OS Development, Part I</a> </li></ul><img style=\"float:right;\" src=\"https://devimages.apple.com.edgekey.net/news/images/feed-images/news_applicationloader.png\"/><br />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:67;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"Exciting New Features in iTunes Connect\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=07282010a\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:748:\"iTunes Connect now offers exciting new features and enhancements. The iTunes Connect Developer Guide (version 6.0) provides details about these features and how you can take advantage of them, including:Using the new Version Release Control to choose when your new app version goes live on the App Store; Delivering binaries using Application Loader; New states for your app including Prepare for Upload, Pending Developer Release, and Processing for App Store;UI Enhancements that indicate when you can edit your app information; Game Center functionality for the setup of Achievements and Leaderboard Categories for sandbox testing purposes. You\'ll find the iTunes Connect Developer Guide available for download on the homepage of iTunes Connect.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 28 Jul 2010 16:38:01 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1043:\"\n<p>iTunes Connect now offers exciting new features and enhancements. The iTunes Connect Developer Guide (version 6.0) provides details about these features and how you can take advantage of them, including:</p><ul class=\"square\"><li>Using the new Version Release Control to choose when your new app version goes live on the App Store; </li><li>Delivering binaries using Application Loader; </li><li>New states for your app including Prepare for Upload, Pending Developer Release, and Processing for App Store;</li><li>UI Enhancements that indicate when you can edit your app information; </li><li>Game Center functionality for the setup of Achievements and Leaderboard Categories for sandbox testing purposes. </li></ul><p>You\'ll find the <a href=\"http://itunesconnect.apple.com/docs/iTunesConnect_DeveloperGuide.pdf\">iTunes Connect Developer Guide</a> available for download on the homepage of iTunes Connect.</p><img style=\"float:right;\" src=\"https://devimages.apple.com.edgekey.net/news/images/feed-images/news_developer_guide.png\"/><br />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:68;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"Announcing iAd for Developers. \nA great way to promote your applications\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=07282010b\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:357:\"The new iAd for Developers program is a great way for you to advertise your own apps to millions of users across the iAd Network. When a user taps on an ad for your app, they can download it from the App Store without leaving the app they\'re in.It\'s easy to get started. Learn more about how you can drive more customers to your app with iAd for Developers.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 28 Jul 2010 16:36:01 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:533:\"\n<p>The new iAd for Developers program is a great way for you to advertise your own apps to millions of users across the iAd Network. When a user taps on an ad for your app, they can download it from the App Store without leaving the app they\'re in.</p><p>It\'s easy to get started. <a href=\"http://developer.apple.com/iad\">Learn more</a> about how you can drive more customers to your app with iAd for Developers.</p><img style=\"float:right;\" src=\"https://devimages.apple.com.edgekey.net/news/images/feed-images/news_iad.jpg\"/><br />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:69;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"\n\n\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"iTunes Connect Mobile App Available\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://developer.apple.com/news/index.php?id=07142010a\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:675:\"The iTunes Connect Mobile (iTC Mobile) app for iPhone allows you to review your sales and related trends, and make informed business decisions while you\'re on the go. You can also view your aggregated unit sales information by product line (e.g., paid apps, free apps, In-App purchases), market (e.g., U.S., France) and individual product. Your information is displayed graphically and can be customized to view select periods of time.The iTC Mobile app for iPhone is available as a free download from the App Store. For detailed instructions on how to take advantage of all the features of iTC Mobile, download the iTC Mobile User Guide from the homepage of iTunes Connect. \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 14 Jul 2010 13:14:07 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:975:\"\n<p>The <a href=\"http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/itunes-connect-mobile/id376771144?mt=8\">iTunes Connect Mobile</a> (iTC Mobile) app for iPhone allows you to review your sales and related trends, and make informed business decisions while you\'re on the go. You can also view your aggregated unit sales information by product line (e.g., paid apps, free apps, In-App purchases), market (e.g., U.S., France) and individual product. Your information is displayed graphically and can be customized to view select periods of time.</p><p>The iTC Mobile app for iPhone is available as a free download from the App Store. For detailed instructions on how to take advantage of all the features of iTC Mobile, download the <a href=\"http://www.apple.com/itunesnews/docs/iTC_Mobile_UserGuide.pdf\">iTC Mobile User Guide</a> from the homepage of iTunes Connect. </p><img style=\"float:right;\" src=\"https://devimages.apple.com.edgekey.net/news/images/feed-images/news_itcmobileapp.png\"/><br />\";s:7:\"attri